.TH BW-SYNC 1 "January 2026" "Bitwarden CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bw-sync \- pull the latest vault data from the server

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw sync
[\fIoptions\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Pull the latest vault data from the Bitwarden server to the local cache.
This synchronizes any changes made on other devices or through the web vault.

The CLI automatically syncs when needed, but you can manually sync to ensure
you have the latest data.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Perform a full sync, replacing all local data.
.TP
.BR \-\-last
Get the date and time of the last successful sync.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Sync vault data:
.nf
$ bw sync
Syncing...
Syncing complete.
.fi
.TP
Force a full sync:
.nf
$ bw sync --force
Syncing...
Syncing complete.
.fi
.TP
Get last sync time:
.nf
$ bw sync --last
2026-01-15T10:30:00.000Z
.fi

.SH NOTES
.TP
\(bu
Requires an active session (vault must be unlocked).
.TP
\(bu
The CLI syncs automatically on most operations.
.TP
\(bu
Use \fB--force\fP if you suspect local data is corrupted or out of sync.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Sync completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Sync failed or error occurred.

